    <name>
      <text>Applying logarithms to a power</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>During a Chemistry laboratory experiment at <strong>Kiharu Comprehensive School</strong>, a chemical sample contained \({@base@}^{@exp@}\) units of <strong>substance X</strong>.</p>

<p>By applying logarithms, write \({@base@}^{@exp@}\) in terms of \(\log {@base@}\).</p>

<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
We use the power law of logarithms:
</p>

<p>
\[
\log(a^n) = n\log a
\]
</p>

<p>
Applying this to the expression:
</p>

<p>
\[
\log({@base@}^{@exp@}) = {@exp@}\log {@base@}
\]
</p>

<p>
So the correct answer is:
</p>

<p>
\[
\boxed{{@exp@}\log {@base@}}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
